                "b": "Before the article",
                "c": "After the noun",
                "d": "After the verb"
            },
            "answer": "c",
            "explanation": "Possessive pronouns always follow the noun they belong to. Example: Το σπίτι μου. (My house.) — never Μου το σπίτι."
        },
        {
            "id": "pr-0041-4000-8000-000000000041",
            "type": "drill",
            "header": "Which is the correct form for 'my name'?",
            "options": {
                "a": "μου το όνομα",
                "b": "το όνομά μου",
                "c": "το μου όνομα",
                "d": "το όνομα"
            },
            "answer": "b",
            "explanation": "Το όνομά μου. The word όνομα is stressed on the 3rd syllable from the end, so it gains a second accent when followed by a weak possessive (double accent rule)."
        },
